<span class="name"><a name="99867"></a></span><span class="postdetails">#1:&nbsp;<font color=black><b>A tip for new enchanter's - Stun Trick</b> Author:&nbsp;<b>Omad</b>,&nbsp;</font></span><span class="postdetails"><font color=black></font></span>
<a href="viewtopic.php?p=99867#99867"><img src="templates/subSilver/images/icon_minipost.gif" width="12" height="9" alt="Post" title="Post" border="0" /></a><span class="postdetails"><font color=black>Posted: Fri Mar 25, 2005 8:05 am</font><span class="gen"><br>
</td></tr>
<tr><td class="printline">
<span class="postbody">I'm sure that most of the enchanter that have been playing for a long time already know of this trick, but I  recently learned of it, and wanted to share it with the noob enchanters.
<br />

<br />
This was taught to me by Fading Illusion of Tunare server.
<br />

<br />
---------------------------------------
<br />

<br />
When charming a mob before you have Dire Charm, charm breaks can make for a really bad day.  There are ways to defuse charm breaks and make life easier on you.
<br />

<br />
Remember those "Color" spells you got and have never used?...well now you're going to use them.
<br />

<br />
Here's what you do.
<br />

<br />
Load up in the spells slots, the three lowest color stuns, lowest to highest going down the spell gems.  Just three will be fine.
<br />

<br />
And yes, even if you're 65, the level 4 stun will work just fine.
<br />

<br />
For me, its Color Flux, Stun, and Skew I believe.  Now that you have them loaded, move the spell slots into the hotkey bank by holding the mouse pointer down until the appear on your pointer, then place them in hotkey 1, 2, and 3, of the empty hotkey bank (i use bank 3).
<br />

<br />
Now, mem your highest charm, and place that spell in the 4th slot of the same bank where you placed your stuns.
<br />

<br />
Your hotkey bank should look like this:
<br />
------ ------
<br />
STUN|STUN
<br />
------|------
<br />
STUN|CHARM
<br />

<br />

<br />
That should be 1, 2, 3, and 4
<br />

<br />
now when charm breaks, when the pet comes up to you, start hitting the stuns in order, 1, 2, 3.  After the third stun, you should have enough time to recharm the your former pet.
<br />

<br />
Another tip is that after you send your pet after something, press F1 twice to retarget your pet.  Durring charm breaks, it can somtimes be very difficult to target your pet again to recharm, the solution is to just keep him targetted.
<br />

<br />
After all three stuns hit your pet (and anything around him) they all will be still for about 3-4 seconds, giving you enough time to recharm.
<br />

<br />
Back up, sick the pet back on one of the mobs, and there you go.  Quick clean and simple.
<br />

<br />
Also if possible, Rune yourself everytime it breaks.  Rune will save your life here.
<br />

<br />
The stuns will also work to stun anything your pet is killing to make him kill faster.  If you are really brave, you can hand him a Proccing mage weapon and throw him a haste.
<br />

<br />
Good luck out there</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
</td></tr>
<br />
